{
  "text": "The DrAChE assay was performed as previously described by [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Briefly, zebrafish brains were homogenized on ice in 60 volumes (v/w) of Triscitrate buffer (50 mM Tris, 2 mM EDTA, 2 mM EGTA, and pH 7.4, with citric acid) using a Potter-Elvehjem-type glass homogenizer. Samples (0.5 g protein) were preincubated for 10 min at 25 ∘ C and the enzyme activity was further assessed in the absence and the presence of the selected compounds. ",
  "correct_citation": {
